-- Nigeria to raise 100 bln naira in 3-, 10-, 20-year bonds
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 07:59AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, July 9 (Reuters) - Nigeria aims to raise 100 billion naira ($615.8 million) in three local currency debt issues on July 16, including its new 20-year bond, the Debt Management Office (DMO) said on Wednesday.

The debt office said it will issue 35 billion naira in the 20-year bond and issue 15 billion naira in the three-year paper and 50 billion naira in the 10-year paper.